    • Method Detail

      • getConnection

        IInteropRestClient getConnection(java.lang.String serverRootURL,
                                 IInteropRestClient.IAuthenticator authenticator)
        Get an instance of the Interop REST client library for a particular server. Such instances should be reused for multiple methods to the same server (rather than creating a new connection each time).

        When the returned client library instance is no longer needed, then IInteropRestClient.shutdown() should be called to free all resources associated with the server connection.

        Parameters:
        serverRootURL - the root URL for Jazz services on the server (e.g. http://localhost:9080/jazz); must not be null
        authenticator - an authenticator callback instance; must not be null
        Returns:
        an instance of the client library for the given server

      • getAdminConnection

        IInteropAdminRestClient getAdminConnection(java.lang.String serverRootURL,
                                           IInteropRestClient.IAuthenticator authenticator)
        Get an instance of the Interop administrative REST client library for a particular server. Such instances should be reused for multiple methods to the same server (rather than creating a new connection each time).

        When the returned client library instance is no longer needed, then IInteropRestClient.shutdown() should be called to free all resources associated with the server connection.

        Parameters:
        serverRootURL - the root URL for Jazz services on the server (e.g. http://localhost:9080/jazz); must not be null
        authenticator - an authenticator callback instance; must not be null
        Returns:
        an instance of the client library for the given server
